markdown: Section on Medical Schools Report Privileged Communication JULY, 1980 ANNUAL BUSINESS MEETING REPORT - JULY 19-20, 1980 AT THE CHICAGO MARRIOTT HOTEL. The Section meeting was attended by 112 Representatives who considered 34 Reports and 48 Resolutions, and prepared testimony for reference committee hearings. Official minutes with final House actions will be included in the agenda of the 1980 INTERIM MEETING SCHEDULED FOR DECEMBER 6TH AT THE SAN FRANCISCO HILTON. ELECTION RESULTS - UNANIMOUSLY REELECTED TO OFFICE FOR A TWO YEAR TERM WERE INCUMBENT OFFICERS DELEGATE, ROBERT S. STONE, M.D., VICE CHAIRMAN, JOHN E. CHAPMAN,MD, AND COUNCILLOR TAMARATH YOLLES, M.D. **FACULTY MEMBERS ELECTED BY HOUSE OF DELEGATES:** **ALAN R. NELSON, M.D.**, UNIVERSITY OF UTAH - BOARD OF TRUSTEES **JACK GIBBS, M.D.**, U OF ILLINOIS, PEORIA - COUNCIL ON MEDICAL EDUCATION **FRANK RIDDICK, M.D.**, TULANE U, LA. - COUNCIL ON MEDICAL EDUCATION **ROBERT D. BURNETT, M.D.**, STANFORD U, CA. - COUNCIL ON MEDICAL SERVICES **JOHN FINKBEINER, M.D.**, CORNELL, N.Y. - COUNCIL ON MEDICAL SERVICES IN HIS INAUGURAL ADDRESS, PRESIDENT ROBERT B. HUNTER, M.D. CITED THE CONTRIBUTIONS, INTEREST AND PARTICIPATION OF MEDICAL EDUCATORS IN THE ASSOCIATION, AS OUTLINED IN THE BROCHURE "AMA'S NEW VOICE IN THE HOUSE - THE ACADEMICIAN". J. LEE DOCKERY, DEAN AT U OF FLORIDA APPOINTED TO AMA'S NEW ADVISORY PANEL ON BIOETHICS - As an adjunct to the Judicial Council, this bioethics panel will consist of a limited group of expert scientific consultants in genetics, biology, chemistry, and physics. THE SECTION GIVES RECOGNITION TO THE FOLLOWING 33 REPRESENTATIVES WHO TESTIFIED BEFORE REFERENCE COMMITTEES REFLECTING SECTION OPINION: WILLIAM C. ALLEN, MO. NEIL ANDREWS, DAVIS, CA. GEORGE BAKER, IOWA STEVEN BEERING, IND RICHARD BAUGHMAN, N.H. EDWARD BRANDT, JR., TX JOHN R. BELJAN, OH GEORGE BRYAN, TX N. CANNON, ALA A. CINOTTI, CMDNJ WM. CROMARTIE, N.C. R. COMBS, IRVINE, CA. MORTON CREDITOR, IL PERRY CULVER, MASS. A.R. DAVIES, OH J.L. DOCKERY, FLA J. ECKSTEIN, IOWA H. HALEY, VA. J.B. HENRY, D.C. L. HIRSCH, IL. ROBERT JOHNSON, SIU L. KETTEL, ARIZ. R. KOHN, BUFFALO PAUL LARSON, LA. J. REINSCHMIDT, ORE WM. SCOTT, AZ DONN SMITH, LA WM. SODEMAN, SR., OH PAT STOREY, PA. R. STONE, TX B. SQUYRES, TX GABE WILSON, UCLA T. YOLLES, STONY BROOK <::logo: American Medical Association AMA AMERICAN MEDICAL ASSOCIATION A circular, monochromatic logo featuring a caduceus symbol in the center, encircled by the organization's full name, and the acronym "AMA" at the top.::> American Medical Association, 535 North Dearborn Street, Chicago, Illinois, 60610, (312) 751-6307 Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/qpbf0227
